This file contains instructions on setting up and running on a Windows system (AI was used to summarise and test this portion)

For Windows,
1) Make sure GitHub and Python are installed

winget install --id Git.Git -e
winget install --id Python.Python.3.11 -e

2) Clone this GitHub repo to your system using

cd C:\Users\Nsega3\Documents
git clone https://github.com/Nsega3/Block-Chain-Analysis.git
cd Block-Chain-Analysis

3) Activate virtual environment (As well as allow Policy bypass: Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1)

python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

4)Install dependencies listed in requirements.txt

pip install -r requirements.txt

5)Create env, to privately input your own API Key 

copy .env.example .env
notepad .env

6)Check output folder exists
mkdir data\outputs

7) Run program 

python -m src.task1_wallet_graph --wallet 0xde0b295669a9fd93d5f28d9ec85e40f4cb697bae --limit 10
